HEADWORD: Ergograph
<hw>Er"go*graph</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ work +
<ets>-graph</ets>.]</ety> <def>An instrument for measuring and recording
the work done by a single muscle or set of muscles, the rate of fatigue,
etc.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Er`go*graph"ic</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ergometer</ent>⟦br⟧
